    <section id="appendix-b" class="kit-page-break">
      <p class="kit-eyebrow kit-section-title">Appendix B &middot; Trustee record-keeping checklist</p>
      <h1>Appendix B — Trustee record-keeping checklist</h1>

      <p>
        Trustees should keep monthly records in a single folder or binder. {state.agencyAbbreviation} may request
        QIT records during periodic eligibility reviews or estate-recovery proceedings. Records also protect the
        trustee personally — fiduciary duty includes the duty to account.
      </p>

      <h3>Monthly file (every month)</h3>
      {hcb ? (
        <ul>
          <li>Trust bank statement showing the month's excess deposit and all payments out.</li>
          <li>Copies of the checks or transfer confirmations for each allowable payment (the applicant's medical and care costs, insurance premiums, allowable trustee or bank fee).</li>
          <li>Receipts or invoices supporting each allowable payment.</li>
          <li>A running note of the trust balance, including any accumulated income carried forward.</li>
        </ul>
      ) : (
        <ul>
          <li>QIT bank statement showing the month's deposit and all distributions.</li>
          <li>Copy of the check (or transfer confirmation) for the Personal Needs Allowance to the applicant.</li>
          <li>Copy of the check (or transfer confirmation) for the spousal allowance, if applicable.</li>
          <li>Copy of the check (or transfer confirmation) for the patient liability to the nursing facility.</li>
          <li>Receipt or acknowledgment from the nursing facility for the patient-liability payment.</li>
        </ul>
      )}

      <h3>Annual file (each calendar year)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Year-end account summary from the bank.</li>
        <li>Income-source statements for the year (SSA 1099, pension 1099-R, VA award letter).</li>
        <li>Copy of any {state.agencyAbbreviation} eligibility-renewal correspondence.</li>
        <li>Copy of any updated trust documents or {state.agencyAbbreviation} template revisions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Permanent file (kept indefinitely)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Original signed trust document.</li>
        <li>Original bank-account opening documents.</li>
        <li>Power of attorney documentation (if applicable).</li>
        <li>Copy of the applicant's Medicaid approval letter.</li>
        <li>Copy of this kit (for the citation chain at the time of setup).</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="kit-cite">
        Retain records for at least seven years after the applicant's death or trust termination, consistent with
        the IRS general statute of limitations and Medicaid estate-recovery timelines.
      </p>
    </section>

